Pumping gas in San Anselmo, Calif. (Justin Sullivan/Getty Images)

Things are more expensive than government statistics say they should be.

A lot of people who watched Rick Santelli blow up on CNBC the other day thought the same thing: “That guy needs a vacation — and so do I. The world just doesn’t make sense to him, or maybe me, either.” So you head up to the cabin. Maybe it’s the same cabin you rented back in 2000, before your kids.
